The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Snatcher arrested
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Snatcher arrested
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	A team from detective department arrested Tapas Das, alias Bulton, on DL Khan Road on Thursday on charges of snatching Rs 12,500 and other valuables from a businessman on Monday.        
	An officer of Hasting police station said Bulton and one of his accomplices, identified as Dhananjay Das, were riding a two-wheeler when they snatched the valuables from the businessmen. Das, too, has been arrested.        
	The two-wheeler has been recovered. The police said Bulton, earlier based in North 24-Parganas, recently shifted to central Calcutta, where he ran an extortion racket.                                                                                                                                                                         
